Talking points to provide to Angelo/Jeff C (Card Connect Leadership Team)
• Status of acquisition
The acquisition of Card Connect by First Data is scheduled to close tomorrow, June 29th.

• Value/message to the ISO community
The Card Connect team is pumped! We are going to pass this positive energy right through our
organization and into our ISO partners.

We can't ignore the fact that the timing of First Data shutting down their largest reseller (BA/Wells)
and acquiring Card Connect is not ideal for the ISO message (to put it lightly).

Regardless, we are moving forward and need a quick resolution with Shift4/Lighthouse.

• Shift4 (Lighthouse) Issue
Our agreement was terminated by Shift4 as a result of the acquisition. We feel the termination was
wrongful.

As the CEO of an organization (Card Connect) that will generate over $50M in profits this year and
as an owner of 2M shares of stock in FDC, I am requesting that we remove emotion from the
equation and address this situation in an extremely professional manner.

I am proposing that we come up with an extremely rich financial incentive that avoids any
probability of us suing the company, First Data, for $100M+.

I have very good relationships with the executive leadership at First Data.

My intentions in our meeting tomorrow are to set a collaborative/positive tone and communicate
that we are willing to sign an agreement that contains non-disparagement language, a 7 year noncompete
for anyone at Card Connect that touches the Shift4 relationship and a full release of any
past/future liabilities.
